[
    {
        "url": "/quotes/nathan_wolfe_563929",
        "quote": "We see new things all the time. We see new retroviruses out there - which is the category that HIV falls into - and we're very, very concerned because this is the part of the world where HIV jumped from chimpanzees to humans.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Nathan Wolfe",
            "url": "/quotes/nathan_wolfe_563929"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "New Things",
                "url": "/topics/new_things"
            },
            {
                "name": "Very",
                "url": "/topics/very"
            },
            {
                "name": "Concerned",
                "url": "/topics/concerned"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/nathan_wolfe_563939",
        "quote": "Seasonal flu is now a pandemic that lasts for years and years because you've got so many people that it's jumping back between northern and southern hemispheres and moving itself around the world. By the time it gets back to where it started, it's changed sufficiently so that people are no longer immune.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Nathan Wolfe",
            "url": "/quotes/nathan_wolfe_563939"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Southern",
                "url": "/topics/southern"
            },
            {
                "name": "Lasts",
                "url": "/topics/lasts"
            },
            {
                "name": "By The Time",
                "url": "/topics/by_the_time"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/nathan_wolfe_563935",
        "quote": "When there is an influenza threat, drop everything and focus on risks from influenza pandemics. When SARS spreads, focus on unknown respiratory diseases. This approach helps to quell public concern, but it's a hugely inefficient way to deal with future risks.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Nathan Wolfe",
            "url": "/quotes/nathan_wolfe_563935"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Deal",
                "url": "/topics/deal"
            },
            {
                "name": "Drop",
                "url": "/topics/drop"
            },
            {
                "name": "Influenza",
                "url": "/topics/influenza"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/nathan_wolfe_563931",
        "quote": "Swine flu is not an anomaly. We know that swine flu - like the vast majority of new outbreaks - comes from animals. We should be monitoring those animals and the humans that come into contact with them, so we can catch these viruses early, before they infect major cities and spread throughout the world.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Nathan Wolfe",
            "url": "/quotes/nathan_wolfe_563931"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "World",
                "url": "/topics/world"
            },
            {
                "name": "Before",
                "url": "/topics/before"
            },
            {
                "name": "Anomaly",
                "url": "/topics/anomaly"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/nathan_wolfe_563923",
        "quote": "If we can provide even a few months of early warning for just one pandemic, the benefits will outweigh all the time and energy we're devoting. Imagine preventing health crises, not just responding to them.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Nathan Wolfe",
            "url": "/quotes/nathan_wolfe_563923"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Just One",
                "url": "/topics/just_one"
            },
            {
                "name": "Pandemic",
                "url": "/topics/pandemic"
            },
            {
                "name": "Benefits",
                "url": "/topics/benefits"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/nathan_wolfe_563925",
        "quote": "With epidemics, people have been standing on the shore, waiting for the gusher to hit the ocean. But to prevent epidemics, you have to look at the various little sources that feed into the river.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Nathan Wolfe",
            "url": "/quotes/nathan_wolfe_563925"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Waiting",
                "url": "/topics/waiting"
            },
            {
                "name": "Been",
                "url": "/topics/been"
            },
            {
                "name": "Sources",
                "url": "/topics/sources"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/nathan_wolfe_563919",
        "quote": "About 20 percent of the genetic information in your nose doesn't match anything that we've ever seen before.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Nathan Wolfe",
            "url": "/quotes/nathan_wolfe_563919"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Nose",
